S4 vendored subset of ferro-compress
====================================

This directory contains a vendored subset of the `ferro-compress` Rust crate,
originally developed as part of the FerroSearch project by:

    abyo software (masumi-ryugo) <abyo.software@gmail.com>

Upstream repository (private):
    https://github.com/abyo-software/ferrosearch-gpu-compress
    crates/ferro-compress/  (Apache-2.0 OR MIT, publish=false)

The files in this directory are dual-licensed under Apache License, Version 2.0
(see LICENSE in this directory) OR the MIT License at the recipient's option.

Files vendored verbatim from upstream `crates/ferro-compress/src/`:
    algo.rs
    error.rs
    nvcomp.rs
    nvcomp_hlif.rs
    bitcomp_device.rs
    slab_alloc.rs
    nvcomp_sys/cuda.rs
    nvcomp_sys/nvcomp.rs
    nvcomp_sys/mod.rs
    cuda_kernels/nvcomp_hlif_shim.cpp
    build.rs

Files modified or rewritten for S4:
    src/lib.rs       — module list trimmed to the nvCOMP-only subset; Tantivy
                       bitmap-op kernel, posting-list stats kernel, CPU codec,
                       and Backend dispatcher are NOT vendored.
    Cargo.toml       — package renamed to `ferro-compress-vendored`,
                       feature surface trimmed to `nvcomp` only, CPU
                       compression dependencies removed.

Third-party dependencies referenced through the vendored FFI bindings:
- NVIDIA nvCOMP — proprietary, distributed under the NVIDIA Software License
  Agreement. Not vendored. Users must obtain libnvcomp.so from NGC and supply
  NVCOMP_HOME at build time. See https://developer.nvidia.com/nvcomp.
- NVIDIA CUDA Toolkit — proprietary. Not vendored. Required at build/runtime.
